ack\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 15, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kyx1665702919550.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kyx1665702919550.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kyx1665702919550.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kyx1665702919550\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Construct the name of the overflow table.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kyx1665702919550__section_N10019_N10016_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d946527e50\">Modes</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kyx1665702919550__d5997e20\">None.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kyx1665702919550__section_N1001E_N10016_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d946527e59\">Conditions</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kyx1665702919550__d6725e20\">None.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kyx1665702919550__section_N10023_N10016_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d946527e68\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kyx1665702919550__p_d152321e1_d152322e1_d152323e1\">This request parses the table name to determine the position of the ‘O’ indicating an overflow table, and changes the table name.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kyx1665702919550__p_d152324e1_d152325e1_d152326e1\">If an occurrence of an entity containing variable-length fields exceeds 8192 bytes, Uniface creates overflow segments that are stored in overflow tables. The overflow table or file has the same name as the main entity, preceded by an ‘O’. The syntax of table names can be too complex to let Uniface place this ‘O’. An example of this is when database, catalogs, database schema names, and separators for these items are included in the entity name. In this case, the Name table request can be used to let the connector place the ‘O’.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kyx1665702919550__p_d152327e1_d152328e1_d152329e1\">The request is provided with a dummy control block. This control block does not describe a table and it does not have an associated connector workspace.</p>\n<div class=\"div\">Refer to:  <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zge1665702663349.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zge1665702663349.html\" title=\"Uniface allows you to access data in multiple DBMSs in a uniform way, simultaneously. The term DBMS is used generically here to describe any structured form of data storage that Uniface understands. According to this definition, a record management system is also a DBMS. All the actions carried out on database tables or files occur via the DBMS interface.\">Uniface Database I/O</a>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529441\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529441\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "N Name table Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 15, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Construct the name of the overflow table. Modes None. Conditions None. Description This request parses the table name to determine the position of the ‘O’ indicating an overflow table, and changes the table name. If an occurrence of an entity containing variable-length fields exceeds 8192 bytes, Uniface creates overflow segments that are stored in overflow tables. The overflow table or file has the same name as the main entity, preceded by an ‘O’. The syntax of table names can be too complex to let Uniface place this ‘O’. An example of this is when database, catalogs, database schema names, and separators for these items are included in the entity name. In this case, the Name table request can be used to let the connector place the ‘O’. The request is provided with a dummy control block. This control block does not describe a table and it does not have an associated connector workspace. Refer to: Uniface Database I/O Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}